# Testing Standards

## Coverage
- Minimum 80% line coverage. Critical paths (event pipeline, hypervisor, auth): 95%+.
- CI blocks PRs that drop below threshold.

## Organization
- Mirror source structure: `src/foo/bar.ts` → `tests/foo/bar.test.ts`
- Group by behavior, not method. Descriptive names: `"flushes buffer immediately on navigation event"`.

## Test types
- **Unit** — isolated, mock externals. **Integration** — real/containerized deps. **E2E** — Playwright (frontend), httpx (backend).
- New features require unit tests. Integration tests when crossing module boundaries.

## Quality
- Deterministic. No flaky tests. Fake timers for timing deps.
- No inter-test state deps. Each test owns its fixtures.
- Test edge cases and error paths. Use factories for test data.

## Before merging
- All tests pass. No skipped tests without linked issue. New code has tests, no exceptions.
